    "summary": "Samir was born in Egypt in 1954 and studied Management and Business Administration at the El Azhar University at Cairo. After graduating he settled in Holland, learning the Dutch Language at the Institute of Applied Linguistics of the University of Nijmegen and studied computer science and information management at the Netherlands Center for Informatics in Amsterdam.\nPartially retired, but still advising top management and helping startup companies creatively create new business.\n\nAs of July 2016, Samir was appointed as EVP and Member of the Board of ImProvia, a leading engineering and contracting company. As of July 2018, Samir focussed on ExRobotics B.V.\nIn 1996 Samir joined Origin International B.V., later Atos. Before being appointed as CEO of Atos Middle East in 2010, he was Global Account Director of Philips Consumer Electronics, Commercial Director for the Akzo Nobel Account and Global Director Pharma Sector. In 2007 he was appointed as Vice President Sales and a member of Atos Origin Sales Management Team.\nIn 2007 he won the Computable Award for a high and innovative IT program in healthcare and in 2008 Samir was chosen Commercial Director of the Year in the Netherlands, singled out for his charisma, long-term vision and personalized approach.\nSeptember 2010, Samir was appointed CEO of Atos Middle East and Africa. After his return to the Netherlands he joined Thales Netherlands where he was leading the commercial innovation process applying Thales\u2019 high value technology in the civilian world and guided the development of tailor-made solutions in the field of healthcare and positioning Thales Cyber security in the Dutch market.\n\nSpecialties: Samir is strongly analytical with a pragmatic approach and a long term vision. He is also strong in organization sensitivity and diplomacy. Samir has a very personalized leadership style and is able to balance a helicopter view with an eye for detail.",
